Description: Power and Sample Size for Health Researchers is a Shiny
        application that brings together a series of functions related
        to sample size and power calculations for common analysis in
        the healthcare field. There are functionalities to calculate
        the power, sample size to estimate or test hypotheses for means
        and proportions (including test for correlated groups,
        equivalence, non-inferiority and superiority), association,
        correlations coefficients, regression coefficients (linear,
        logistic, gamma, and Cox), linear mixed model, Cronbach's
        alpha, interobserver agreement, intraclass correlation
        coefficients, limit of agreement on Bland-Altman plots, area
        under the curve, sensitivity and specificity incorporating the
        prevalence of disease. You can also use the online version at
        <https://hcpa-unidade-bioestatistica.shinyapps.io/PSS_Health/>.
URL: https://hcpa-unidade-bioestatistica.shinyapps.io/PSS_Health/
